cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about improving natural language understanding using multi-sense embeddings. The paper discusses various natural language understanding tasks such as part-of-speech tagging, named entity recognition, sentiment analysis, semantic relation identification, and semantic relatedness. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new model based on Chinese Restaurant Processes, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of embeddings, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses named entity recognition, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
